@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    This door is a companion to the @{"FreeDL" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/FreeDL.Guide/MAIN} Door.

    When an uploaded file is about to be placed in a conference the door
    is called, it then looks in that conference's directory for a file
    called MakeFreeDLList.TXT.  If that file is not found then
    HBBS:System/Data/MakeFreeDLList.TXT is looked for.

    If a file is found it is loaded and comments are stipped from the file.
    Then each line of that file is compared (case-insensitively and wild
    cards) is compared to the file name of the uploaded file.

    If a match is found in the list it will add the filename of the uploaded
    file to the conference's FreeDLList.TXT file, it will then post a message
    to a specified recipient list informing them that the file is a free
    download.

    A user specified comment is then added to the file list.

    The difference between this door and the FreeDL door is that the
    FreeDL door actually makes the files free downloads, this door is used
    to automatically post messages to users.

    You may find you'd rather have some wildcard lines in the FreeDLList.TXT
    files rather than the MakeFreeDLList.TXT files if you don't want
    messages to be posted but you still want the files to be free.

    E.G.

    Say you have a HBBS Conference:

    HBBS:Conferences/HBBS/MakeFreeDLList.TXT

    cP!-H#?
    docs.lha

    or a normal file conference:

    HBBS:Conferences/FileConf1/MakeFreeDLList.TXT

    dc-#?
    flt-#?
    cP!-#?

    You could also have *every* single file uploaded into a conference
    made free, and have a message posted about it by having just "#?"
    as the only line in the conference's MakeFreeDLList.TXT file.
    This is great for distribution sites!


@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The door is stored as:

    HBBS:Doors/System/MakeFreeDL/MakeFreeDL.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.05.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to a Commands/System file (HBBS:Commands/System is
    recommended).

    AddDIZToList_Type_2=HBBS
    AddDIZToList_Door_2=HBBS:Doors/System/MakeFreeDL/MakeFreeDL.HBBS {N} {O}

    It is recommended that the door be called after all other doors that
    deal with adding the .DIZ to the file list so that this door can
    add data to the file list in the right place.

    Edit the config file:

    HBBS:Doors/System/MakeFreeDL/MakeFreeDL.CFG

    Create MakeFreeDLList.TXT files in each conference and in
    HBBS:System/Data as required.

@EndNode

